From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] musb: gadget: rate-limited RX anomaly diagnostics (bulk-OUT
 stall investigation)

Temporary instrumentation for the sustained bulk-OUT stall (large adb
push / fastboot boot through usb-proxy). Two traces, both silent unless
the anomaly actually occurs:

 * musb_g_rx(): log OVERRUN/INCOMPRX with RXCOUNT and the full RXCSR.
   Either flag on an OUT endpoint means the controller dropped or
   mangled a packet the host believes was ACKed -- the suspected
   failure mode. The stock code clears these flags silently.

 * musb_ep_restart() RX requeue path (added by patch 0001): log if the
   FLUSHFIFO fallback ever runs with FIFOFULL set while RXPKTRDY is
   clear, a state where flushing would destroy received data.

Applies on top of 0001-musb-gadget-service-pending-RX-packet-on-requeue.
Remove once the stall investigation concludes.

Signed-off-by: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
---
 drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c | 25 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 23 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c
@@ -818,6 +818,19 @@
 	musb_dbg(musb, "<== %s, rxcsr %04x%s %p", musb_ep->end_point.name,
 			csr, dma ? " (dma)" : "", request);
 
+	/*
+	 * Diagnostic (usb-proxy appliance): OVERRUN or INCOMPRX on an OUT
+	 * endpoint means the controller dropped or mangled a packet the host
+	 * believes was ACKed -- the failure mode suspected in the sustained
+	 * bulk-OUT stall. The stock code clears these flags silently.
+	 */
+	if (csr & (MUSB_RXCSR_P_OVERRUN | MUSB_RXCSR_INCOMPRX))
+		pr_info_ratelimited("musb rx-diag: %s csr %04x count %d%s%s\n",
+				musb_ep->end_point.name, csr,
+				musb_readw(epio, MUSB_RXCOUNT),
+				(csr & MUSB_RXCSR_P_OVERRUN) ? " OVERRUN" : "",
+				(csr & MUSB_RXCSR_INCOMPRX) ? " INCOMPRX" : "");
+
 	if (csr & MUSB_RXCSR_P_SENTSTALL) {
 		csr |= MUSB_RXCSR_P_WZC_BITS;
 		csr &= ~MUSB_RXCSR_P_SENTSTALL;
@@ -1190,6 +1203,15 @@
 		if (csr & MUSB_RXCSR_RXPKTRDY) {
 			rxstate(musb, req);
 		} else {
+			/*
+			 * Diagnostic: flushing with FIFOFULL set but RXPKTRDY
+			 * clear would destroy received data in a state the
+			 * driver does not expect; scream if it ever happens.
+			 */
+			if (csr & MUSB_RXCSR_FIFOFULL)
+				pr_info_ratelimited("musb rx-diag: %s requeue flush with FIFOFULL, csr %04x count %d\n",
+						req->ep->end_point.name, csr,
+						musb_readw(epio, MUSB_RXCOUNT));
 			csr |= MUSB_RXCSR_FLUSHFIFO | MUSB_RXCSR_P_WZC_BITS;
 			musb_writew(epio, MUSB_RXCSR, csr);
 			musb_writew(epio, MUSB_RXCSR, csr);
